<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1085,1434,1573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1183">
D i s t r i b u t i o n a n d n a t u r a l h i s t o r y The confirmed distribution is confined to 
<collectingCountry box="[308,364,1463,1485]" name="Israel" pageId="4" pageNumber="1183">Israel</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[422,541,1463,1485]" name="West Bank" pageId="4" pageNumber="1183">West Bank</collectingCountry>
. The species has been reported also from 
<collectingCountry box="[996,1084,1463,1485]" name="Lebanon" pageId="4" pageNumber="1183">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="SMETANA A" box="[186,352,1493,1515]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1183" pagination="505 - 698" refId="ref17730" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Staphylinidae, subfamilies Omaliinae - Dasycerinae, Phloecharinae - Apaticinae, Piestinae - Staphylininae, pp. 237 - 272, 329 - 495, 505 - 698. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds): Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. II. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. - Stenstrup, Apollo Books: 942 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA 2004</bibRefCitation>
), but this record requires revision. The external morphology (broad body; short antennae) suggests that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saulcy" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[562,700,1522,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Astenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platynotus">
<emphasis box="[562,700,1522,1543]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1183">A. platynotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be associated with ants of the genus 
<emphasis box="[243,376,1552,1573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1183">Tetramorium</emphasis>
MAYR, 1855.
</paragraph>
